{"name":"Witcher Kit","flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"pagetype":"text"},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.O7s9KIorqMZ2R2EY"},"cf":{"id":"temp_0o8y5afw0so"}},"pages":[{"type":"text","name":"Witcher Kit","_id":"Dpeh8rrXN1quCaFk","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\">Tier 1 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Prepared Brewing </strong>– With one hour of work, which can be accomplished over a short rest, you can brew up to 3 vials of Potion Serums or Weapon Oils by utilizing the formulae you know and expending the appropriate resources.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Potion Serums</strong> – A Serum can be readily drunk or administered to an unconscious or willing creature as an Action. Administering a Serum to an unwilling creature requires a Dexterity (Sleight of Hand) check contested by the creature’s Strength (Athletics), Dexterity (Acrobatics), or Dexterity (Sleight of Hand) check (their choice). If you are hidden from the creature you make your check with Advantage and they have Disadvantage on their check.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Vial Belt</strong> – You have a specialized arm or leg band that can hold up to 3 vials of Serums. Drinking one of these vials only requires a Bonus Action. You can add vials to the band as an action.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Weapon Oils</strong> – Oils can be applied to a weapon as an action. If you possess the Poisoner Feat, you may apply oils as a Bonus Action. Oils persist on the weapon until a successful attack is made.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Formulae</strong></span></p><ul><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Nighteye Serum</strong> (25 gold)<br />Grants the drinker an additional 60 feet of Darkvision for one hour.</span></p></li><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Lullaby Serum</strong> (25 gold)<br />Puts the drinker to sleep for one hour. Upon waking, the drinker gains the benefits of a short rest and recovers one level of exhaustion.</span></p></li><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Minor Healing Serum</strong> (25 gold)<br />The drinker regains 2d4 hitpoints and an additional 2d4 at the start of its turn for three turns.</span></p></li><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Physical Impact Oil</strong> (25 gold)<br />Deals 2d6 damage of the weapon’s type.</span></p></li><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Elemental Impact Oil</strong> (25 gold) (Fire, Acid, Cold, Lightning, Poison)<br />Deals 2d6 damage of the associated type on a successful hit.</span></p></li><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Elemental Lingering Oil</strong> (25 gold) (Fire, Acid, Cold, Lightning)<br />A creature hit with a weapon coated in this oil must make a Dexterity Saving Throw against your Kit DC. On a failure, the creature’s body is coated by the oil and they take 2d4 damage of the appropriate type at the start of their turn for three turns.</span></p></li></ul><h2><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\">Tier 1 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Aptitude</strong> – You gain a magical +1 bonus to your Kit DC and your proficiency in using the kit as a standard tool.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Aetheric Infusion</strong> – Any weapon coated in one of your oils is considered magical for the purposes of bypassing damage resistance.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Formulae</strong></span></p><ul><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Esoteric Impact Oil</strong> (50 gold) (Force, Psychic, Radiant, Necrotic)<br />Deals 2d6 damage of the associated type on a successful hit.</span></p></li><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Esoteric Lingering Oil</strong> (50 gold) (Force, Psychic, Radiant, Necrotic)<br />A creature hit with a weapon coated in this oil must make a Wisdom Saving Throw against your Kit DC. On a failure, the creature’s body is coated by the oil and they take 2d4 damage of the appropriate type at the start of their turn for three turns.</span></p></li><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Wolverine Serum</strong> (100 gold)<br />For one hour, while the drinker’s hitpoints are below half of their maximum, they deal an additional 2d6 Piercing damage with weapon attacks.</span></p></li></ul><h2><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\">Tier 2 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Additive Agents</strong> – You have learned how to brew Additive Agents that can be added to your Oils, Poisons, and Serums.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\">Additive Agents are somewhat volatile, you may only carry 4 such agents at one time.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\">When you use an action to apply an oil or administer a serum, you may use a Free Action to add an Additive Agent first, granting the oil or serum an additional effect.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Brewing Efficiency</strong> – You can now brew a total of 4 Oils or Serums and 2 Additive Agents for each hour of work.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Canister Bombs</strong> – With ten minute’s work you can craft a single bomb by utilizing the formulae you know and expending the appropriate resources.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\">Canister bombs are considered a ranged weapon with a range of 30 feet. If you are proficient with using the kit, you are proficient in throwing the bombs.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Canister Bandolier</strong> – You have a bandolier which can hold 5 canister bombs. You can draw and throw a bomb in place of any attack you make. Storing canister bombs anywhere other than your bandolier can be extremely hazardous.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Vial Belt</strong> – You have an additional vial belt, allowing you to carry a total of 6 Serums at the ready.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Formulae</strong></span></p><ul><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Glue Bomb</strong> (100 gold)<br />On impact creates a 10-foot radius area of difficult terrain. Each creature within the radius on impact must make a Dexterity Saving Throw against your Kit DC. On a failure, they become Restrained by the rapidly hardening glue. As an Action, a Restrained creature may attempt to break free of the glue by making a Strength (Athletics) or Dexterity (Acrobatics) Check against your Kit DC.</span></p></li><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Poison Bomb</strong> (100 gold)<br />On impact releases gas in a 10-foot radius sphere. Each creature in the sphere must make a Constitution saving throw against your Kit DC. On a failure the creature takes 3d8 Poison Damage and is Poisoned for one minute. On a success a creature takes half damage and is not Poisoned. A Poisoned creature can repeat the save at the end of each of its turns.</span></p></li><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Healing Serum</strong> (150 gold)<br />The drinker regains 3d8 hitpoints and an additional 3d8 at the start of its turn for three turns.</span></p></li><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Willow Serum</strong> (150 gold)<br />The drinker becomes immune to the Grappled, Paralyzed, Prone, Restrained, and Stunned conditions for one minute.</span></p></li><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Steroid Serum</strong> (150 gold)<br />Doubles the drinker’s short range with all thrown weapons for one hour.</span></p></li><li><p><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Concentrated Distilling Agent</strong> (50 gold)<br />The weapon oil bypasses damage resistance.</span></p></li><li><p><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Adaptive Distilling Agent</strong> (50 gold)<br />The weapon oil imposes Disadvantage on the save made to resist it.</span></p></li><li><p><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Physical Fortifying Agent</strong> (50 gold)<br />5 points of Damage Reduction against Bludgeoning, Piercing, or Slashing damage (you choose when you add the agent to a serum).</span></p></li><li><p><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Elemental Fortifying Agent</strong> (50 gold)<br />Resistance to Acid, Fire, Cold, Lightning, or Poison damage (you choose when you add the agent to a serum).</span></p></li></ul><h2><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\">Tier 2 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Enhanced Aptitude</strong> – The bonus from Aptitude increases to +2.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Stabilized Agents</strong> – You can now carry 8 Additive Agents.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Formulae</strong></span></p><ul><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Wolf Serum</strong> (250 gold)<br />The drinker’s Critical Hit Threshold with Melee Weapons is reduced by 1 for one hour.</span></p></li><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Stoneskin Serum</strong> (250 gold)<br />The drinker gains</span><span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\">  </span></span><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\">a +1 bonus to AC and Resistance to all Bludgeoning, Piercing, and Slashing damage for 1 hour.</span></p></li><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Esoteric Fortifying Agent</strong> (100 gold)<br />Resistance to Radiant, Necrotic, Psychic, or Thunder damage (you choose when you add the agent to a serum).</span></p></li><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Holy Water Bomb</strong> (200 gold)<br />On impact splashes holy water in a 10-foot radius, each hostile creature in the area must make a Dexterity Saving Throw against your Kit DC. On a failure the creature takes 4d8 Radiant Damage. On a success the creature takes half damage. Undead and Fiends make this save at Disadvantage.</span></p></li></ul><h2><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\">Tier 3 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Rapid Mixing</strong> – You may now brew a total of 6 Oils or Serums and 4 Additive Agents for each hour of work spent brewing.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Canister Bandolier</strong> – You have a second bandolier, allowing you to carry a total of 10 Canister Bombs safely.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Vial Belt</strong> – You have an additional vial belt, allowing you to carry a total of 9 Serums at the ready.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Stabilized Agents</strong> – You can now carry 10 Additive Agents.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Formulae</strong></span></p><ul><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Bottled Rage</strong> (500 gold)<br />The drinker gains a +4 bonus to all Attack Rolls at the cost of a -2 penalty to AC and Dexterity Saving Throws for 1 minute.</span></p></li><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Greater Healing Serum</strong> (500 gold)<br />The drinker regains 4d12 hitpoints and an additional 4d12 at the start of its turn for three turns.</span></p></li></ul><h2><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\">Tier 3 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Enhanced Aptitude</strong> – The bonus from Aptitude increases to +3.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Stabilized Agents</strong> – You can now carry 12 Additive Agents.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}}}],"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1676868205294,"modifiedTime":1677091734539,"lastModifiedBy":"gaqhLuQlqSyM3GkX"},"ownership":{"default":0,"eRgA1h4qRUhZdwPz":3,"gaqhLuQlqSyM3GkX":3},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"09LtzyVAPUuuxwoU"}
{"name":"Sapphie's Lyre","flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"pagetype":"text"},"scene-packer":{"hash":"7db2908f29c413cbefecf70a04caf3c5c96b1d60","sourceId":"JournalEntry.4RCxyHsQsI4ogFGc"},"exportSource":{"world":"might-and-mercenaries","system":"dnd5e","coreVersion":"10.291","systemVersion":"2.1.4"},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.NgiiB1T6jkdfr9UO"},"cf":{"id":"temp_77t4r2kc60q"}},"pages":[{"type":"text","name":"Sapphie's Lyre","_id":"0nWfgyH0Lj1a2dAp","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 1 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Lilting Performance</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> As an action you can play a lively tune to regain one use of Bardic Inspiration. You can do this performance once per Long Rest.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 1 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Passion</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You gain a +1 bonus to Spell Attack rolls and the Save DC of your spells.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Compassionate Song</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> When you cast a spell that restores hitpoints, you can roll 1d4 and add the total rolled to the amount restored.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 2 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Lilting Expert</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Your Lilting Performance can now be performed once per Short Rest.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 2 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Greater Passion</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The bonus from Passion increases to +2.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Welling Compassion</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The bonus from your Compassionate Song increases to 1d6.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 3 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Lilting Virtuoso</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Your Lilting Performance now regains all expended uses of Bardic Inspiration.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 3 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Superior Passion</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The bonus from Passion increases to +3.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Boundless Compassion</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The bonus from your Compassionate Song increases to 1d8.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}}}],"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1676062833244,"modifiedTime":1677091161697,"lastModifiedBy":"gaqhLuQlqSyM3GkX"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"eRgA1h4qRUhZdwPz":3},"_id":"4zLDXXnVDLD5CFbA"}
{"name":"Artificer's Bladed Tech Staff","flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"pagetype":"text"},"scene-packer":{"hash":"9e454996f164a6f8d830d78aa7d0ee8fc84cee65","sourceId":"JournalEntry.qfP5wFe8mFejS7Wg","defaultPermission":2},"exportSource":{"world":"might-and-mercenaries","system":"dnd5e","coreVersion":"10.291","systemVersion":"2.1.4"},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.H5QzrqoKapNWLrU8"},"cf":{"id":"temp_0t5s1gpbcib"}},"pages":[{"type":"text","name":"Artificer's Bladed Tech Staff","_id":"4ddQSso51RU2R1Rz","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>Tier 1 Mundane</h2><p><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Aetheric Flow</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> This weapon can be used as a focus for casting spells.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Serrated Blade</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> Cruel serrations have been added along the length of the blade. Any melee attack made with the Staff deals an additional 2 Slashing Damage.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Telescoping Shaft</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> Attacks made with the staff on your turn have a range of 10 feet.</span></p><h2>Tier 1 Magical</h2><p><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Mechanized Assistance</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> You gain a +1 Bonus to Weapon and Spell Attack and Damage rolls and the save DC of spells cast using the staff as a focus.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Aetheric Overcharge</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> You can add your Intelligence modifier to the damage roll of any spell cast through the staff.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Specialized Tool</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> If you have any of the following class features, you gain the corresponding benefit</span></p><ul><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Thunder Gauntlets<br></strong>A creature hit by the staff has disadvantage on attack rolls against targets other than you. With each attack, you can choose to deal Thunder damage instead of the weapon</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">s normal damage.</span></p></li><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Lightning Launcher<br></strong>The bonus from Mechanized Assistance applies to attacks made with your Lightning Launcher. You can channel the additional lightning damage into any weapon attack made with the staff. You can still only deal the bonus damage once per turn.</span></p></li></ul><h2>Tier 2 Mundane</h2><p><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Harmonic Resonator</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> A Harmonic Resonator has been installed in the blade of the staff, allowing for a wide range of effects when the appropriate amount of aether is fed into it.</span></p><ul><li><p><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Upkeep</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> Certain effects of the Resonator require a continual upkeep of power in addition to the up-front cost to trigger the effect. Upkeep is accomplished as a Free Action at the start of your turn.</span></p></li></ul><p><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Aether Trap</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> An aether trap is attached to the staff to allow for the directed release of power into the Harmonic Resonator. The trap has a capacity of 20 charges and passively absorbs aether from everything around it at a slow rate. At the end of a Long Rest, the trap gains 1d8 + 4 charges.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Feed the Trap</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> As an Action, you can directly feed aether into the trap in the form of essence.</span></p><ul><li><p><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">Uncommon Essence </span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> 3 charges</span></p></li><li><p><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">Rare Essence </span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> 6 charges</span></p></li><li><p><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">Very Rare Essence </span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> 10 charges</span></p></li></ul><p><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Resonating Blade</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> As a Bonus Action you can unleash 5 charges from the Aether Trap to activate the Harmonic Resonator, causing the blade to vibrate intensely. Maintaining this vibration requires an upkeep cost of 1 charge. While the blade is vibrating, Weapon Attacks made with the staff gain a +1 Bonus to the Attack Roll and deal an additional 2d4 Force Damage with each hit.</span></p><h2>Tier 2 Magical</h2><p><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Overcharged Rotors</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> The bonus provided by your Mechanized Assistance increases to +2. You ignore half and three-quarters cover for any attack roll made with the staff.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Harnessed Lightning</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> As a Bonus Action you can unleash 6 charges into the resonator to cause it to begin harnessing energy, causing lightning to coalesce and play about the blade. Maintaining this effect requires an upkeep cost of 1 charge. While the blade is shrouded in lightning you can use an Action to unleash a directed bolt. Pick a point you can see within 40 feet of the staff, each creature within 5 feet of that point must make a Dexterity Saving throw with a DC equal to 8 + proficiency bonus + your Attack Bonus with the staff. On a failed save the creature takes 3d10 lightning damage, or half as much on a success.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Directed Power</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> By funneling differing amounts of aether from the trap into the resonator you are able to replicate a variety of spell effects. These effects function much like the spells they replicate, including the action type required. No material component is required other than the resonator itself. Any other adjustments are specifically noted. The save DC of these effects is equal to 8 + your Attack Bonus with the staff.</span></p><ul><li><p><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">1 Charge </span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> Booming Blade, Lightning Lure, Spare the Dying</span></p></li><li><p><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">2 Charges </span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> Thunderwave, Gift of Alacrity (Only 2 instances can be active at the same time), Protection from Energy (Thunder Damage only, no concentration required)</span></p></li><li><p><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">4 Charges </span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> Silvery Barbs, Blur (Can target other people, the target of the spell maintains the concentration), Silence (in an aura around the staff)</span></p></li><li><p><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">6 Charges </span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">Counterspell, Dispel Magic, Lightning Bolt, Pulse Wave, Haste (the target of the spell maintains the concentration)</span></p></li><li><p><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">10 Charges </span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> Revivify</span></p></li></ul><h2>Tier 3 Mundane</h2><p><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Enlarged Trap</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> Your Aether Trap now has a capacity of 30 charges.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Rapid Harnessing</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> Once per day, you can trigger your Trap to more aggressively harvest aether from any sources nearby. After one hour, which can coincide with a Short Rest, the trap recovers 1d12 + 4 charges. Actively using the trap by feeding it with essence or powering the resonator interrupts this process.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Violent Resonation</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> By unleashing 8 charges into the blade you can achieve an even more destructive level of vibrations. Maintaining this level of vibration requires an upkeep cost of 2 charges. While the blade is vibrating in this fashion, Weapon Attacks made with the staff gain a +2 Bonus to the Attack Roll and deal an additional 3d8 Force Damage with each hit.</span></p><h2>Tier 3 Magical</h2><p><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Nanite Infusion</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> The bonus provided by your Mechanized Assistance increases to +3.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Essence Leech</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> Your Aether Trap has been modified to capture the aether that typically escapes when a creature dies or is grievously wounded. When a non-trivial (per the DM</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">s discretion) creature within 10 feet of you is reduced to 0 hitpoints or suffers a critical hit the trap gains 1d4+2 charges.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Power Overwhelming</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> You</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">ve gained the ability to cause even more effects by channeling aether into the resonator.</span></p><ul><li><p><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">8 Charges </span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> Banishment (Range is touch, and the creature is not banished but held in stasis while concentration is maintained)</span></p></li><li><p><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">10 Charges </span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> Wall of Force (the wall must originate within 10 feet of the staff), Cone of Cold (Deals Thunder Damage), Destructive Wave (Deals Lightning instead of Radiant or Necrotic Damage)</span></p></li><li><p><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">20 Charges </span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> Raise Dead</span></p></li></ul>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}}}],"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672556705949,"modifiedTime":1677098796057,"lastModifiedBy":"gaqhLuQlqSyM3GkX"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"eRgA1h4qRUhZdwPz":3},"_id":"8vszYI3gxClJLsqU"}
{"name":"Trinity, Thor's Thunderous Smite","flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"pagetype":"text"},"scene-packer":{"hash":"6c38f7ece5b091f96ec809b40a4797e312f0b482","sourceId":"JournalEntry.dJjULaZfv93L9qMJ","defaultPermission":2},"exportSource":{"world":"might-and-mercenaries","system":"dnd5e","coreVersion":"10.291","systemVersion":"2.1.4"},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.Y6JcZ3gt3k2VYQJF"},"cf":{"id":"temp_r3uvjq13w9"}},"pages":[{"type":"text","name":"Trinity, Thor's Thunderous Smite","_id":"ruTzShIX0GX7F1bR","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">Ashe</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">s gift from the God of Thunder, Thor. The weapon itself has a connection with Thor, when he</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">s not off drinking himself under the table.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top: 12.0pt; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 0in; margin-left: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong>Temperament. </strong></span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">Loyal, Cruel</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong>Weapon. </strong></span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">Warhammer</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong>Awakening Phrase. </strong></span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">TBD</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong>True Awakening Durability. </strong></span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">12.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong>Toll. </strong></span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">You suffer one level of exhaustion. Additionally, you take 4d6 lightning damage and have disadvantage on all attack rolls until you finish a long rest.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family: EBGaramond-Regular\">Base Traits</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong>Godly Favor. </strong></span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">Trinity gains the following properties while you are attuned to it: <em>Thrown (30/60), Returning, Magical, Focus</em></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong>Imbued Hammer. </strong></span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">Trinity deals an additional 1d8 Thunder Damage on each hit.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong>Aetheric Channeling. </strong></span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">You gain a +1 bonus to your Spell Save DC.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong>Thor’s Might</strong></span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">. As a Free Action when you attack with Trinity, you can invoke Thor</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">s Might. If you do, you don</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">t let go of the handle and instead it pulls you through the air after it. If the Attack hits, you can immediately use a Bonus Action to make an additional Melee Attack against the same target. Whether the Attack hits or misses, you end adjacent to the target. You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Proficiency Bonus and regain all uses after a Long Rest.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family: EBGaramond-Regular\">Awakening</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">When Trinity awakens, intense lightning begins to arc about the head of the weapon.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong>Improved Aetheric Channeling</strong></span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">. The bonus from Aetheric Channeling increases to 2.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong>Giant’s Bane</strong></span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">. Trinity deals an additional 1d8 Bludgeoning Damage against any creature larger than you.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong>Thor’s Wrath</strong></span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>. </strong>While Awakened, you can use an Action to cast Lightning Bolt at 5</span><sup><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">th</span></sup><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> level. The damage is maximized as if you had used the Destructive Wrath Channel Divinity, but you don</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">t expend a use of that feature. You can use this ability twice and regain all uses when you regain the ability to Awaken Trinity.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong>Limited Flight.</strong></span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> While Awakened, you are blessed with a limited flight. Your flight speed increases by 10 and you are able to hover freely in the air. You may invoke Thor</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">s Might at will without expending a use.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family: EBGaramond-Regular\">True Awakening</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">When you activate Trinity</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">s True Awakening, Thor recognizes you as his true emissary, as such he allows Trinity to act as a conduit for the full might of his divine prowess. The head of the hammer begins to glow and crackle as if it were made of solidified lightning, you gain the following benefits.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong>Greater Aetheric Channeling. </strong></span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">The bonus from Aetheric Channeling increases to 3.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong>Thor’s Fury. </strong></span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">Until the True Awakening ends, crackling thunder clouds swirl high over your head. The cloud has a 30-foot radius and moves with you, remaining centered on you. As a Bonus Action you can reduce your True Awakening Durability by 3 to call down a Bolt of Lightning as from the Call Lightning spell cast at 9</span><sup><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">th</span></sup><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\"> level.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong>Echoes of Mjolnir</strong></span><span style=\"font-family: CrimsonText-Regular\">. While Truly Awakened, each successful melee attack with Trinity causes small bolts of lightning to emanate from the hammer. Choose up to 3 other targets within 30 feet of the creature you hit. Those creatures must make a Dexterity Saving Throw, suffering 3d8 Lightning Damage on a failure or half as much damage on a success.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}}}],"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674594915256,"modifiedTime":1677091054067,"lastModifiedBy":"gaqhLuQlqSyM3GkX"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"eRgA1h4qRUhZdwPz":3},"_id":"AV2ZILYSO0uquOyp"}
{"name":"Azazel Scythe","flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"pagetype":"text"},"scene-packer":{"hash":"77a15e030ab546ce0a36e54db01f9b9f12f8c630","sourceId":"JournalEntry.sMHUJIhnNtpRhQ8t","defaultPermission":2},"exportSource":{"world":"might-and-mercenaries","system":"dnd5e","coreVersion":"10.291","systemVersion":"2.1.4"},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.4Ab5EzWlNAyB6phQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_0t5s1gpbcib"}},"pages":[{"type":"text","name":"Azazel Scythe","_id":"z9YaBX9MRBzaEkhC","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>Initial Item</h2><h4>War Scythe</h4><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><strong>Damage</strong> – 1d8 Slashing + 1d6 Force</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><strong>Versatile Damage</strong> – 1d10 Slashing + 1d8 Force</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\">Martial Weapon, Infernal Weapon, Versatile</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\">Infernal Weapon – Attacks with an Infernal Weapon can be made using Charisma, rather than Strength or Dexterity.</p><p>Versatile - While wielded in two hands the scythe has the reach property.</p><h2>Tier 1 Mundane</h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><strong>Lethality</strong> – You gain a +1 bonus to Attack and Damage rolls.</p><p><strong>BloodHound Stance</strong> - As a bonus action you can enter a cyclone stance, which lasts until the end of your next turn or until you end it as a free action. While in the stance your speed is reduced to 0 and every melee attack you make on your turn hits every target of your choice within range. If you have not yet used an action to attack on your turn, ending the stance restores your movement speed. You can enter the stance a number of times equal to your proficiency modifier and you regain all uses on a long rest.</p><h2>Tier 1 Magical</h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><strong>Malice</strong> - You gain 1 additional use of baleful interdict.</p><p><strong>Absorb Despair</strong> - When you score a critical hit, you regain one use of baleful interdict.</p><p><strong>Disciplined Authority</strong> - You now have 2 uses of Invoke Authority, but they must be used on different features.</p><h2>Tier 2 Mundane</h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><strong>Improved Lethality</strong> – The bonus from Lethality increases to +2.</p><p><strong>Razor's Edge</strong> - The additional force damage dealt with each hit increases.</p><h2>Tier 2 Magical</h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><strong>Greater Malice</strong> - You gain 1 additional use of baleful interdict.</p><p><strong>Emboldened Authority</strong> - Invoke Authority now regains its uses on a short rest.</p><p><strong>Ample Despair</strong> - When you score a critical hit, you regain a use of infernal conduit.</p><h2>Tier 3 Mundane</h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><strong>Greater Lethality</strong> – The bonus from Lethality increases to +3. Your critical hit threshold is reduced by 1.</p><h2>Tier 3 Magical</h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><strong>Superior Malice</strong> - You gain 1 additional use of baleful interdict.</p><p><strong>Empowered Authority</strong> - You now have 3 total uses of Invoke Authority but only 2 uses can be used on the same feature.</p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}}}],"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675300737232,"modifiedTime":1677091128545,"lastModifiedBy":"gaqhLuQlqSyM3GkX"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"eRgA1h4qRUhZdwPz":3},"_id":"CGkBFJoGpBW7gJZg"}
{"name":"Survivalist's Pouch","flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"type":"text"},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.CwQMykmCzMU59TZd"},"cf":{"id":"temp_0t5s1gpbcib"}},"pages":[{"type":"text","name":"Survivalist's Pouch","_id":"sf3fshktUf0fbSWg","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<ul><li><p>Bedroll</p></li><li><p>Two-Person Tent</p></li><li><p>Tinderbox</p></li><li><p>Mess Kit</p></li><li><p>250 Feet of Rope</p></li><li><p>Grappling Hook</p></li><li><p>10 Foot Pole</p></li><li><p>10 Foot Ladder</p></li><li><p>Crowbar</p></li><li><p>Sledgehammer</p></li><li><p>Miner's Pick</p></li><li><p>Hammer</p></li><li><p>20 Pitons</p></li><li><p>20 Iron Spikes</p></li><li><p>Shovel</p></li><li><p>Portable Ram</p></li><li><p>Block and Tackle</p></li><li><p>Lantern</p></li><li><p>5 Flasks of Oil</p></li><li><p>2 Sets of Clothing</p></li><li><p>Snowshoes</p></li><li><p>20 Rations</p></li><li><p>5 Waterskins</p></li><li><p>Iron Pot</p></li><li><p>Rain Catcher</p></li><li><p>Fishing Tackle</p></li><li><p>Tools (Artisan's, Kits, etc.)</p></li><li><p>5 Containers of Ammunition</p></li><li><p>2 Pouches with up to 500 coins each</p></li></ul>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}}}],"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671572860348,"modifiedTime":1677091140456,"lastModifiedBy":"gaqhLuQlqSyM3GkX"},"_id":"CwQMykmCzMU59TZd","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Oz2iQtljCOeEAeBW":3}}
