{"name":"Tom's Fancy Hat","flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"pagetype":"text"},"scene-packer":{"hash":"b23cc6a9e9676e64aeaabd3a19d5fb8d52504e52","sourceId":"JournalEntry.elmPptVexPAaFOnO"},"exportSource":{"world":"might-and-mercenaries","system":"dnd5e","coreVersion":"10.291","systemVersion":"2.1.4"},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.FHzFtavWLjxcA1qK"},"cf":{"id":"temp_0o8y5afw0so"}},"pages":[{"type":"text","name":"Tom's Fancy Hat","_id":"QnPkaypRcNP7IKjI","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 1 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Glamerweave</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The hat is made out of the finest Glamerweave, allowing for basic illusory patterns to be manifested within or rising from the cloth. When you make a Charisma Ability Check, you can roll 1d4 and add it to the result. You may do this a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus, and you regain all uses at the end of a long rest.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 1 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Essence Weaving</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Essence infused threads have been woven throughout the hat. You gain a magical +1 bonus to Armor Class and Saving Throws.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>What</strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong>’</strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>s In the Hat?</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Several extra dimensional pockets have been sewn within the lining of the hat.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Pocket of Holding</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> This pocket is a basic extra dimensional space. It functions as a standard Bag of Holding but can only hold 100 pounds.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Pocket of Bones</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> This pocket can hold up to 10 medium corpses or undead creatures. It violently expels anything else placed within it. A corpse or willing creature can be placed in the pocket as an Action. You can withdraw a single corpse or creature as an Object Interaction, or empty the entire pocket as an Action.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 2 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Uncommon Glamerweave</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The Glamerweave within the hat has been further enhanced. You now add 1d6 to every Charisma Ability Check you make while wearing it.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 2 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Hat of Invisibility</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> An enchantment has been added to render the hat completely invisible. As a free action you can turn the enchantment on. The enchantment can be active for a total of one hour, tracked in one-minute increments. If you are wearing the hat, you can choose to have the enchantment turn yourself invisible as well but it drains 10 minutes of power for each 1 minute it is active in this way. The enchantment regains 10 minutes of use each hour after a period of twelve hours of not being used.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Pocket of Life</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> As an Action, you or a willing creature within 5 feet can enter this pocket. The pocket fully sustains the creature inside for 1 hour, after which the creature will begin to suffocate if they don</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">t leave. A creature inside the pocket can leave at any time as a Free Action. Once a creature enters the pocket, no other creature can enter until the end of a Long Rest.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Essence Infusion</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The magical bonus from Essence Weaving increases to +2.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 3 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Essence Infusion</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The magical bonus from Essence Weaving increases to +3.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Mansion in a Hat</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> As an Action you can pull a magical door out of the hat. Up to 20 creatures of your choice can pass through the doorway in to an extradimensional dwelling as per the Mordenkainen</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">s Magnificent Mansion spell. After 24 hours the dwelling dissipates and the door vanishes, expelling anything from outside to the ground near the door. The dwelling will dissipate early if no living creatures remain inside. After the door vanishes, a new one can</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">t be pulled from the hat for 8 hours.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}}}],"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675727440234,"modifiedTime":1677091163328,"lastModifiedBy":"gaqhLuQlqSyM3GkX"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"eRgA1h4qRUhZdwPz":3},"_id":"DLZQfg9tokTTqKEq"}
{"name":"Lineage & Legacy","flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"pagetype":"text"},"scene-packer":{"hash":"21207f22cb83302bb1b525da8333bc903332a82a","sourceId":"JournalEntry.VhL76MtIwWsRxwUB","defaultPermission":2},"exportSource":{"world":"might-and-mercenaries","system":"dnd5e","coreVersion":"10.291","systemVersion":"2.1.4"},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.P9knQOGSBW9QQ9mL"},"cf":{"id":"temp_r3uvjq13w9"}},"pages":[{"type":"text","name":"Lineage & Legacy, Blades of Eternal Glory","_id":"pWlpnS0f5HIaAFNr","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">These ancestral blades belong to the Corwin dynastic line. They were long since thought lost forever, with most believing them to be only myth until they were located, recovered, and reunited by their current wielder Raeyan Corwin.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong>Temperament. </strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">Bold, Cunning, Inspiring. Occasionally makes jokes or offers words of encouragement.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong>Weapon. </strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">Longsword and Shortsword</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong>Awakening Phrase. </strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">Remember.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong>True Awakening Durability. </strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">12.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong>Toll. </strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">You suffer one level of exhaustion. Additionally, your movement speed is halved until the end of your next long rest.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong>Joined Weapons. </strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">Both swords are considered a single magical item for the purposes of attunement. If one blade moves more than 120 feet from the other, the person attuned to the blades can have the blade which is further away teleport to their hand.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Base Traits</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong>Generational Memories.</strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You are able to draw on the experience of previous wielders of the blades and gain the following benefits while attuned to the weapons:</span></p><ul><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">Lineage gains the finesse property.</span></p></li><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">Legacy gains the thrown property. If you know the Mage Hand cantrip, you can throw Legacy up to the maximum range of your mage hand. Otherwise, you can throw it 20 feet.</span></p></li><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">After being thrown, Legacy returns to your hand.</span></p></li><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">Legacy can be used as an arcane focus. Also, you are able to perform the somatic components of spells with your hand while it is wielding Legacy.</span></p></li></ul><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong>Enhanced Blades. </strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">Lineage deals an additional 1d8 piercing damage. Legacy deals an additional 1d6 slashing damage.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong>Cunning Blade. </strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">You can use a bonus action to either throw or swing Legacy at a creature within range. Make a melee attack against that creature. This attack is eligible for sneak attack as long as you do not have disadvantage and haven</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">t already used sneak attack this turn.</span></p><p></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Awakening</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">When you awaken Lineage and Legacy, they begin to glow with a soft inner light. If you have a use of Bladesong available, it activates.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong>Flurry</strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">. While awakened, you can use your action to gain the effects of the Haste spell for 1 minute. This invocation of the spell doesn</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">t require concentration and has no ill effects when it ends.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong>Generational Fury</strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">. While awakened, you can use your action to unleash the fury of your ancestors. Each creature of your choice within the throwing range of Legacy must make a Dexterity Saving Throw as the blade leaves your hand and darts about in a frenzy. On a failed saving throw, a creature takes 3d6 slashing damage and 3d6 piercing damage and their speed is halved until the end of your next turn. On a successful save they take half as much damage and no other effects. You can use this ability twice, and regain all uses on a long rest.</span></p><p></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">True Awakening</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">When you activate Lineage and Legacy</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">s True Awakening, the blades grow brighter and faint whispers can be heard emanating from them. You also activate the Flurry effect as part of the same action.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong>Ancestral Premonitions. </strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">Until the True Awakening ends, you have the benefits of the Foresight spell as your awakened ancestors predict the flow of battle and whisper warnings of what is to come.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong>Pinpoint Strike. </strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">The number required to land a critical hit is reduced by 1. In addition, if the total you roll to hit is 30 or higher, it is also considered a critical hit.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong>Generational Inspiration</strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">. When you fail a saving throw or skill check or miss with an attack roll, you may call upon your familial ancestors to offer inspirational encouragement or advice. If you do, reduce your True Awakening Durability by 1 and add a 1d12 bardic inspiration die to the triggering roll.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}}}],"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672578841669,"modifiedTime":1677091059305,"lastModifiedBy":"gaqhLuQlqSyM3GkX"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"eRgA1h4qRUhZdwPz":3},"_id":"FwAPT72AH6IFVTQ7"}
{"name":"Diligence, Bulwark Against Betrayal","flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"pagetype":"text"},"scene-packer":{"hash":"42651e184628f1d6b8b7eab89345e284876f4d98","sourceId":"JournalEntry.X2FcQSr2cKJS2MoB","defaultPermission":2},"exportSource":{"world":"might-and-mercenaries","system":"dnd5e","coreVersion":"10.291","systemVersion":"2.1.4"},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.KUUJUmhwLelHJXaj"},"cf":{"id":"temp_0o8y5afw0so"}},"pages":[{"type":"text","name":"Diligence, Bulwark Against Betrayal","_id":"zc6xLnFLxSXHcwkf","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">This round metal shield is covered in countless Dwarven runes recounting episodes of betrayal and lapses in judgement.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Requires Attunement by a Dwarf.</strong> A Non-Dwarf may attempt to attune to the shield, to do so they must make a DC 20 Wisdom Saving Throw. On a success, they master the shield and attune to it, on a failure they are overwhelmed by grief and anger and fall unconscious for 2d4 hours. They must complete a week</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">s worth of long rests before attempting the attunement again.</span></p><p></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 1 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Custom Fitted Straps</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> This property is only in effect while the shield is properly donned on your arm. These straps have been custom designed to provide a better fit, allowing greater control of the shield. The base AC Shield bonus provided by the shield is increased by 1. As a reaction to being attacked by an enemy you can see, you focus your efforts on wielding your shield more effectively, doubling the base AC bonus against the attack.</span></p><p></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 1 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Racial Aptitude</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> While attuned to this shield you are considered proficient with shields if you would not otherwise be.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Vigilant Reminder</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The stories of betrayal decorating the shield provide a constant reminder of the need for vigilance. You gain advantage on Perception and Insight checks and can't be surprised.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Runic Etchings</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The stories written on the shield are interspersed with runes of protective power providing a magical +1 bonus to AC and Saving Throws.</span></p><p></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 2 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Deflecting Angles</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You have learned to interpose your shield to help deflect harmful spells and effects. Add the base AC bonus of the shield to Dexterity Saving Throws against spells or other effects that deal damage.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Quick Release Buckles</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The straps of your shield are fitted with quick release buckles, allowing you to doff the shield as a Free Action.</span></p><p></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 2 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Ardent Shield</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Runic empowerment has imbued a certain sense of liveliness into the shield. As a Bonus Action you can speak a command word, causing the shield to doff itself from your arm if you have it equipped and begin circling around you defensively. While it is circling, you can use a Bonus Action to speak another command word and cause it to don itself on your arm if you have an empty hand. The shield can be animated for a total of 10 minutes, tracked in 1-minute increments. At the end of this time the shield falls lifeless to the ground wherever it is. Over a long rest the shield regenerates 1d10 minutes of energy up to a maximum of 10.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">While it is circling, when an ally you can see within 30 feet of you is hit with an attack, you can direct your shield to intercede as a Reaction. Add the total AC bonus provided by the shield to the target</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">s AC, potentially causing the attack to miss. After the attack is resolved, the shield returns to circling around you.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Hale and Hearty</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Your Constitution score is increased by 2 to a maximum of 20.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Well Rounded</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">– </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">Pick an ability score other than Constitution that you don</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">t use as your primary attack stat for martial characters or your primary casting stat for primary spell casters. That ability score is set to 18. Work with your DM to determine the most appropriate ability score.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Runic Engravings</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Further runes of power are added to the shield. The magical bonus to AC and Saving Throws is now 2.</span></p><p></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 3 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Quick Locking Buckles</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> To the uninitiated these buckles appear to be nothing short of magic, allowing you to don the shield as a bonus action.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Shield Master</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Rigorous training has allowed you to become an expert in utilizing the defensive properties of your shield. If you are subjected to an effect that allows you to make a Dexterity saving throw to take only half damage, you can use your reaction to take no damage if you succeed on the saving throw.</span></p><p></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 3 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Runic Inscription</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Interspersed amongst the runes of power can be found an Ancient Dwarven Inscription reading: </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\"><em>“</em></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><em>Never Forget. Never Forgive.</em></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\"><em>”</em></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><em> </em>The magical bonus to AC and Saving Throws provided by the shield is increased to 3.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Spellguard</strong> - You have advantage on saving throws against spells and other magical effects, and spell attacks have disadvantage against you.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}}}],"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672566437434,"modifiedTime":1677091099239,"lastModifiedBy":"gaqhLuQlqSyM3GkX"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"eRgA1h4qRUhZdwPz":3},"_id":"HM1uphmxP9igZ3AB"}
{"name":"Blooming Rose","flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"pagetype":"text"},"scene-packer":{"hash":"6f468a8e64a567cdf68185f159004feae42c508c","sourceId":"JournalEntry.8V25NI8ccRwuM2sq"},"exportSource":{"world":"might-and-mercenaries","system":"dnd5e","coreVersion":"10.291","systemVersion":"2.1.4"},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.bI2wTNZbqRtTwcyj"},"cf":{"id":"temp_77t4r2kc60q"}},"pages":[{"type":"text","name":"Blooming Rose","_id":"SESBoEXKxPkll8VD","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Initial Item</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in\"><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Katana</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Damage</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> 1d8 Slashing</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Weapon DC</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> 8 + Proficiency Bonus + Dexterity Bonus</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">Finesse</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 1 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Lethality</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You gain a +1 bonus to Attack and Damage rolls and your Weapon DC.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Petal Slash</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Whenever you hit a creature with a melee attack you can inflict an additional 1d4 Slashing Damage to the target or another creature within 5 feet of the target.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Petal Swarm</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> When a creature within 5 feet of you or your Echo hits you or your Echo with a melee attack you can use a reaction to roll 1d4 and subtract the number rolled from the attack roll.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 2 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Sharpened Blade</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The base damage of the blade increases to 1d8 + 1d4.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Blooming Rose Technique</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> As an action you can begin performing an intricate pattern of movements with your blade, causing petals to manifest and spin about in a 10-foot diameter vortex around you. The vortex moves with you, remaining centered on you. This technique lasts for 10 minutes and requires you to maintain concentration, as if concentrating on a spell.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">While this technique is active you can</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">t take reactions, but can direct streams of petals outwards, giving your melee attacks a range of 30 feet.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">The vortex only affects creatures of your choice, and those creatures</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> speed is halved while in the vortex. When a creature enters the vortex for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, it must make a Dexterity Saving Throw. On a failed save, the creature takes 4d8 Slashing Damage. On a successful save, the creature takes half damage.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">You can use this technique once, and regain the ability to do so after a Long Rest.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 2 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Improved Lethality</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The bonus from Lethality increases to +2.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Guardian Petals</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You now roll 1d6 when using Petal Swarm and it can be triggered by an attack against an ally as well as yourself. The creature making the attack must still be within 5 feet of either you or your Echo.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">While Blooming Rose Technique is active, Petal Swarm can be triggered by any creature within the vortex and you can use Petal Swarm against a number of attacks per round equal to your Dexterity Modifier. You still can</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">t take any other Reactions.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Deep Reserves</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The radius of Blooming Rose Technique increases to 15 feet and you can use it twice, regaining all uses on a Long Rest.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 3 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Thorns Among the Petals</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Petal Slash now also inflicts 2d4 Piercing Damage. The Petal Vortex from Blooming Rose Technique now also inflicts 4d4 Piercing Damage.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>The Duality of Man</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Your Echo now also manifests a Petal Vortex when you use Blooming Rose Technique.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 3 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Greater Lethality</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The bonus from Lethality increases to +3. Your Critical Hit threshold is reduced by 1.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>White Rose Blade</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> While Blooming Rose Technique is active, you can use a Free Action at the start of your turn to end the vortex early and concentrate all the energy in to your blade. If you do, the base damage of the blade changes to 4d12 Force Damage until the end of your turn.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}}}],"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1676063121620,"modifiedTime":1677091173994,"lastModifiedBy":"gaqhLuQlqSyM3GkX"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"eRgA1h4qRUhZdwPz":3},"_id":"HqEqILRN8M3Bnmfk"}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_77t4r2kc60q","name":"Friday","color":"#000000","fontColor":"#FFFFFF","icon":"","sorting":"m","contents":["pVX6WLkRn2iZ4TEv","w0WY6Agn9Lmy4tSF","4zLDXXnVDLD5CFbA","itJSYwIXuCdef687","ou1GfzbSKnE5uMAY","TnDXIHdES6Zap6FY","HqEqILRN8M3Bnmfk"],"children":[],"folderPath":["temp_yws72co531"]}},"pages":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"gaqhLuQlqSyM3GkX":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677091151138,"modifiedTime":1677091173994,"lastModifiedBy":"gaqhLuQlqSyM3GkX"},"_id":"QOgl9FFcd5AxgWnj"}
{"name":"Supremacy Ammo Types","flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"type":"text"},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.QpkaM3tPITowCNCa"},"cf":{"id":"temp_0t5s1gpbcib"}},"pages":[{"type":"text","name":"Supremacy Ammo Types","_id":"8W2AsH4QqsGXETkT","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h3>Tier 1 - 25 gold</h3><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Deadly</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You gain a +1 Bonus to Attack and Damage rolls.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Elemental Payload</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Choose Fire, Cold, Lightning, Acid, or Poison, each piece of ammunition deals an additional 1d4 damage of the chosen element.</span></p><h3>Tier 2 - 75 gold</h3><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Devastating</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You gain a +2 bonus to Attack and Damage rolls.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Elementally Infused</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Choose Fire, Cold, Lightning, Acid, or Poison, each piece of ammunition deals an additional 1d8 damage of the chosen element.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Pummeling</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> This ammunition deals Bludgeoning damage instead of Piercing. A creature hit with this ammunition must make Strength Saving Throw against your Weapon DC or fall prone. Concentration checks made as a result of damage from this ammunition are made at disadvantage.</span></p><h3>Tier 3 - 250 gold</h3><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Cataclysmic</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Gain a +3 Bonus to Attack and Damage rolls.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Blunderbuss </strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> This ammunition taps in to the use of an extradimensional space to deliver a larger payload than should be possible. When you fire a piece of Blunderbuss ammunition, your weapon discharges a 20-foot Cone of Shrapnel instead of a single projectile. Make a ranged attack roll with your weapon at each target in the cone, dealing 4d12 damage on a successful hit.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}}}],"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671573977385,"modifiedTime":1677091135053,"lastModifiedBy":"gaqhLuQlqSyM3GkX"},"_id":"QpkaM3tPITowCNCa","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Oz2iQtljCOeEAeBW":3}}
{"name":"Bracers of the Totem Warrior","flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"pagetype":"text"},"scene-packer":{"hash":"c6d001ea96a522e83b20df345ba915eef8f3c582","sourceId":"JournalEntry.JVDnCNjFtFSdjQM6","defaultPermission":2},"exportSource":{"world":"might-and-mercenaries","system":"dnd5e","coreVersion":"10.291","systemVersion":"2.1.4"},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.fwrUqCWPVeYNpKOw"},"cf":{"id":"temp_77t4r2kc60q"}},"pages":[{"type":"text","name":"Bracers of the Totem Warrior","_id":"w5WoskL30WYC9p77","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 1 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Sustain the Rage</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> If your rage is going to end at the end of your turn, you can use a free action to sustain it. You can do this a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus and you regain all uses at the end of a long rest.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Shamanistic Training</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You have substantial teachings in tapping in to the totemic spirits of your people. Whenever you finish a long rest, choose one Totem Spirit that you did not choose as part of your class training, you gain the effect of that spirit until you take your next long rest.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 1 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Runic Etchings</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Runes of power are etched in to the bracers. You gain a +1 bonus to Armor Class and Saving Throws.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 2 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Subdued Recklessness</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> When you use your Reckless Attack feature, you can choose to do so in a more controlled manor. If you do, you take a -2 penalty to your Attack Rolls on this turn but you do not grant Advantage on attack rolls against you.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Enhanced Shamanism</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You may now choose an Aspect of the Beast with your Shamanistic Training. You still only choose one feature.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 2 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Runic Engravings</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The magical bonus from Runic Etchings increases to +2.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 3 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Mastered Shamanism</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You now choose two features with your Shamanistic Training, and you may also choose Totemic Attunements.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 3 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Runic Inscription</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The magical bonus from Runic Etchings increases to +3.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}}}],"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675455933308,"modifiedTime":1677091171540,"lastModifiedBy":"gaqhLuQlqSyM3GkX"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"eRgA1h4qRUhZdwPz":3},"_id":"TnDXIHdES6Zap6FY"}
{"name":"Reckoning, Legacy of Vengeance","flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"pagetype":"text"},"scene-packer":{"hash":"6e93725368c4bedada780012563d63bb76cfaf35","sourceId":"JournalEntry.KxXLCHNo7oj9PyMG","defaultPermission":2},"exportSource":{"world":"might-and-mercenaries","system":"dnd5e","coreVersion":"10.291","systemVersion":"2.1.4"},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.MzxFMfNgWga4xeqX"},"cf":{"id":"temp_0o8y5afw0so"}},"pages":[{"type":"text","name":"Reckoning, Legacy of Vengeance","_id":"Qk1Myqc7TlTL4ztA","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">To properly achieve vengeance requires two things: a healthy dose of fury directed at the one who did you wrong and perhaps paradoxically, restraint. So it is with the legendary weapon Reckoning, which can manifest as either the mighty hammer Restraint or the fearsome axe Fury.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Requires Attunement by a Dwarf.</strong> A Non-Dwarf who can speak Dwarven may attempt to attune to the weapon by making a DC 20 Persuasion Check. On a success they are allowed to attune to the weapon for one year, after which they must make the check again to continue the attunement. On a failed check, the attunement fails and the character is forbidden from attempting to attune to the weapon for one month. If they try again after one month, the DC of the Persuasion Check is increased by 5. After 6 months of not attempting to attune to the weapon, the DC is reduced by 5 to a minimum of 20.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 1 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Silveranvil Puzzle Handle</strong> - The handle of this weapon incorporates a clever design originally meant for jewelry puzzles made by the Silveranvil clan. The handle can be easily extended or collapsed and firmly locked in place. The handle has two notches, One Handed and Two Handed. As an object interaction you can either extend or collapse the handle to change between them.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Spiked Head</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> A wicked backspike has been added to the head of the weapon. Attacks with the weapon will now do a modicum of piercing damage.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 1 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Racial Aptitude</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> While attuned you gain proficiency in this weapon if you don</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">t otherwise have it.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Runic Etchings</strong> - Runic designs have been etched in to the head of the weapon to enhance your power. You gain a +1 bonus to Attack and Damage rolls made with the weapon, as well as a +1 Bonus to Spell Attacks and the Save DC of Spells cast using this weapon as a focus.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 2 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Counter-Balance</strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\"><strong> </strong>–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> A counterweight has been added to the handle to improve the stability while in flight, allowing you to throw the weapon further without losing accuracy.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Flanged Head</strong> - The design of the head of the weapon has been further enhanced to increase the piercing damage dealt with each hit.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 2 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Runic Engraving</strong> - Additional Patterns have been added to the runic etchings on the head of the weapon, increasing the attack, damage, spell attack, and spell DC bonus to 2.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Malleable Identity</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> A sentience has been bound in to the head of Reckoning. While the metal appears to be entirely solid and sound, it is actually in a constant state of flux. With a one-hour ritual, which can be accomplished over a short rest, you can entice the weapon to solidify in one of two forms: the hammer head of Restraint, or the axe blade of Fury.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Grudge Bearer</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> It</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">s common knowledge that Dwarves are amongst the best at holding grudges. When that energy is infused in to a sentient weapon, the drive to settle a grudge can become truly terrifying. Check with your DM if your enemies qualify for any of the following grudges, and if so apply the appropriate bonus to all attacks made against them with Reckoning.</span></p><ul><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">Minor Grudge </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Someone who insulted you, your friends, or your clan. Against such a target you gain a +2 bonus to damage rolls.</span></p></li><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">Moderate Grudge </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Someone caused you material loss in some fashion. Whether due to incompetence, malfeasance, or just bad luck is irrelevant, it</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">s unacceptable. Against such a target you gain a +2 bonus to attack and damage rolls.</span></p></li><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">Major Grudge </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Someone who caused a loss of life or something similarly tragic. Against such a target you gain a +2 bonus to attack and damage rolls, and all attacks against them are made with advantage.</span></p></li><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">Legendary Grudge </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> If you have one of these, you know. This is the grudge that keeps you up at night and keeps you going through any obstacle to get even. Against such a target, all attacks are made with advantage, you gain a +3 to attack and damage rolls, and all hits are critical hit.</span></p></li></ul><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 3 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Improved Puzzle Handle</strong> - You have further improved upon the interlocking handle of the weapon, allowing it to be extended in length to become a pole weapon. The handle now has three notches. As an object interaction you can extend or collapse the handle by one notch, as a Bonus Action you can fully extend or collapse the handle.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Powerful Blows</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> This property only functions while Restraint is the active Identity. Deal double damage to structures, objects, and constructs. When you hit a creature or construct with an attack, you can push them up to 10 feet with the force of the blow.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Keen Edge</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> This property only functions while Furor is the active Identity. Your weapon attacks score a critical hit on a roll one lower than normal.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 3 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Runic Inscription</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The etched patterns in the head of Reckoning grow ever more complex, flowing throughout them is the Firemane clan motto: </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\"><em>“</em></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><em>We Can, We Will, We Did</em>.</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">”</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The attack, damage, spell attack, and spell DC bonus is increased to 3.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Rapid Adaptation</strong> - You</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">ve gained greater control over the behavior of the weapon. As a Bonus Action, you can cause the weapon to assume the identity of Restraint or Fury. You can do this a number of times equal to your proficiency modifier, and you regain all uses when you finish a long rest.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Watchful Gaze</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> This property only functions while Restraint is the active Identity. When a creature within the near attack range of your weapon makes an attack against a target other than you, you can use your reaction to make a weapon attack against the creature. If as a result of your attack the target of the creature</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">s attack is no longer in range, the creature</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">s attack fails.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Brutal Blows</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> This property only functions while Fury is the active Identity. Whenever you roll the maximum value on a weapon die, roll the die again and add the result. If you roll the maximum value again, keep rolling and adding the result until you don</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">t roll the maximum value.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Manifest Identity</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The sentience within Reckoning has grown more powerful and is able to manifest that power to devastating effect depending on which Identity is active and what configuration the weapon handle is in. Your Weapon DC is equal to 8 + your attack bonus while wielding the weapon. You can unleash this power a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus and you regain all uses after a long rest.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}}}],"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672561860791,"modifiedTime":1677091107154,"lastModifiedBy":"gaqhLuQlqSyM3GkX"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"eRgA1h4qRUhZdwPz":3},"_id":"WMzNNBCGqzfjiBrT"}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_0t5s1gpbcib","name":"Wednesday","color":"#000000","fontColor":"#FFFFFF","icon":"","sorting":"m","contents":["8vszYI3gxClJLsqU","s4xyrfTblr0QvFpO","CGkBFJoGpBW7gJZg","jZjI1qUha3eTYWnt","QpkaM3tPITowCNCa","XqUAJNbYu6dgFyPN","CwQMykmCzMU59TZd","YtuJcCCKZKPjRMTe"],"children":[],"folderPath":["temp_yws72co531"]}},"pages":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"gaqhLuQlqSyM3GkX":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677091114073,"modifiedTime":1677091143535,"lastModifiedBy":"gaqhLuQlqSyM3GkX"},"_id":"XchiQCZr9w5lbOcO"}
{"name":"Supremacy, Fusil of Retaliation","flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"type":"text"},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.XqUAJNbYu6dgFyPN"},"cf":{"id":"temp_0t5s1gpbcib"}},"pages":[{"type":"text","name":"Supremacy, Fusil of Retaliation","_id":"YPeZLBwNKuWwWl9F","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 1 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Enhanced Sights</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You have upgraded the sights on the rifle. Your short and long range are both doubled with this weapon.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Ammo Smithing</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">ve learned to craft your own bullets efficiently. With one hour</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">s work you can craft 10 basic bullets provided you have access to suitable scrap materials.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Canister Bombs</strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You have learned to craft crude explosives that will detonate on impact. With ten minute</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">s work and 50 gold worth of materials you can craft one of the following types of bombs: <strong>Poison, Blaze, Shrapnel</strong>.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">You have a bandolier which can hold 5 canister bombs. You can draw and throw a bomb in place of any attack you make. Thrown canister bombs have a range of 15 feet. Storing canister bombs anywhere other than your bandolier can be extremely hazardous.</span></p><p>@UUID[Compendium.garhis-custom-stuff.garhis-custom-journals.QpkaM3tPITowCNCa]{Supremacy Ammo Types}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.garhis-custom-stuff.garhis-custom-journals.YtuJcCCKZKPjRMTe]{Canister Bombs}</p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 1 Magical</span></h2><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Lethality</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You gain a +1 Bonus to Attack and Damage rolls made with this weapon.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Targeting Guidance</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You can tap in to embedded magic within the weapon to enhance your aim as a Bonus Action. When you do, you deal an additional 1d6 Piercing damage with the weapon for one hour. You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Proficiency Bonus, and you regain all uses on a long rest.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Arcane Ammo Smithing</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">ve learned to infuse magic in to ammunition you craft. By using 25 gold worth of materials, you can craft one of the following types of ammunition instead of basic ammunition: <strong>Deadly, Elemental Payload</strong></span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 2 Mundane</span></h2><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Canister Launcher</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> A launching tube is attached to the bottom of your rifle to allow you to launch canister bombs a decent distance. Instead of throwing a canister, you can load it in to the launcher and fire it. Launched canisters have a range of 40 feet.</span></p><p>The bonus from Lethality applies to the Save DC of your bombs.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Improved Canister Bombs</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You have learned to craft more potent versions of your canister bombs using 100 gold worth of materials: <strong>Mephitic Poison, Conflagration, Fragmentation</strong>.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 2 Magical</span></h2><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Improved Lethality</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The bonus from Lethality increases to +2.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Expert Arcane Ammo Smith</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You have developed improved ways of binding magic to ammunition. With 75 gold worth of materials, you can craft one of the following types of ammunition instead of basic ammunition: <strong>Devastating, Elemental Infused, Pummeling</strong>.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 3 Mundane</span></h2><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Master Ammo Smith</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You have become even more efficient at crafting your own ammunition. You can now craft 20 pieces of ammunition with the time and resources it would normally take to craft 10.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Enhanced Rifling</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Upgrades to the barrel of the weapon allow for more accurate shots that penetrate deeper. The base damage of the weapon increases to <strong>2d12 Piercing</strong>.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Efficient Launching</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Launched Canisters now have a range of 60 feet.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Deadly Cannisters</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You have devised even deadlier cannister bombs using 500 gold worth of materials: <strong>Virulent Poison, Inferno, Fulminating</strong>.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 3 Magical</span></h2><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Greater Lethality</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The bonus from Lethality increases to +3. Your critical hit threshold is reduced by 1.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Master Arcane Ammo Smith</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">You have learned to craft the following types of ammunition using 250 gold worth of materials: <strong>Cataclysmic, Blunderbuss</strong></span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}}}],"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671573681398,"modifiedTime":1677097738408,"lastModifiedBy":"gaqhLuQlqSyM3GkX"},"_id":"XqUAJNbYu6dgFyPN","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Oz2iQtljCOeEAeBW":3}}
{"name":"Canister Bombs","flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"type":"text"},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.YtuJcCCKZKPjRMTe"},"cf":{"id":"temp_0t5s1gpbcib"}},"pages":[{"type":"text","name":"Canister Bombs","_id":"ZVgsdyyhzHbQUDaX","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h3>Tier 1 - 50 gold - Thrown - 15 feet</h3><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Poison</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> On impact releases gas in a 10-foot radius sphere. Each creature in the sphere must make a Constitution saving throw against your Weapon DC. On a failure the creature takes 3d8 Poison Damage and is Poisoned. On a success a creature takes half damage and is not Poisoned. A Poisoned creature can repeat the save at the end of each of its turns.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Blaze </strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> On impact creates a 5-foot cube of fire that persists for 5 rounds. Any creature that enters the flames for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there takes 2d4 fire damage.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Shrapnel </strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> On impact releases a concussive wave filled with flying debris. Each creature within a 10-foot radius of the point of impact must make a Dexterity saving throw against your Weapon DC. On a failure the creature takes 3d6 Piercing Damage and any movement speed it has is halved until the end of its next turn. On a success a creature takes half damage and no other effect.</span></p><h3>Tier 2 - 100 gold - Launched - 40 Feet</h3><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Mephitic Poison</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> On impact releases concentrated gas in a 10-foot radius sphere. Each creature in the sphere must make a Constitution saving throw against your Weapon DC. On a failure the creature takes 5d8 Poison Damage and is Poisoned. On a success a creature takes half damage and is not Poisoned. A Poisoned creature can spend an action to attempt to shake off the poison by repeating the saving throw.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Conflagration </strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> On impact creates a 10-foot cube of roaring fire that persists for 5 rounds. Any creature that enters the flames for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there takes 2d8 fire damage.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Fragmentation </strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> On impact releases a concussive wave filled with flying debris. Each creature within a 15-foot radius of the point of impact must make a Dexterity saving throw against your Weapon DC. On a failure the creature takes 6d6 Piercing Damage and any movement speed it has is halved until the end of its next turn. On a success a creature takes half damage and no other effect.</span></p><h3>Tier 3 - 500 gold - Lofted - 60 Feet</h3><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Virulent Poison</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> On impact releases concentrated gas in a 15-foot radius sphere. Each creature in the sphere must make a Constitution saving throw against your Weapon DC with Disadvantage. On a failure the creature takes 8d8 Poison Damage and is Poisoned. On a success a creature takes half damage and is not Poisoned. A Poisoned creature can spend an action to attempt to shake off the poison by repeating the saving throw with Disadvantage.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Inferno </strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> On impact creates a 15-foot cube of raging fire that persists for 5 rounds. Any creature that enters the flames for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there takes 3d12 fire damage.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Fulminating </strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> On impact releases a concussive wave filled with flying debris. Each creature within a 20-foot radius of the point of impact must make a Dexterity saving throw against your Weapon DC. On a failure the creature takes 6d6 Piercing Damage and 4d6 Thunder Damage and any movement speed it has is halved until the end of its next turn. On a success a creature takes half damage and no other effect.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}}}],"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671574126208,"modifiedTime":1677091143535,"lastModifiedBy":"gaqhLuQlqSyM3GkX"},"_id":"YtuJcCCKZKPjRMTe","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Oz2iQtljCOeEAeBW":3}}
{"name":"Kivi's Symbiote","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"Kivi's Symbiote","type":"text","_id":"V7pzccWKQLxFwy1m","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">Flavor Text</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:12.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Temperament. </strong>TBD</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Equipment. </strong>A symbiotic lifeform that lives within the body</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Awakening Phrase. </strong>TBD</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>True Awakening Durability.</strong> N/A</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Toll. </strong>You suffer two levels of exhaustion and lose all benefits of the symbiote until you finish a long rest.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">Base Traits</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Hammerfists.</strong> Your fists are especially punishing. Whenever you make an unarmed attack using your fists, you roll 2 of your Martial Arts dice.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Manifest Barbs</strong>. As a bonus action, you can manifest a number of barbed spines equal to a roll of your Martial Arts Die + your Proficiency Bonus. These barbs can then be launched with a range of 60 feet in place of any unarmed attack you would make. They do not benefit from Hammerfists. When you Manifest Barbs any remaining barbs from previous manifestations are first reabsorbed in to your body. While you have Barbs Manifested, you have Advantage on Charisma (Intimidation) Ability Checks.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">Awakening</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">When you Awaken your symbiote, it begins to take more direct control. [[TODO: List physical characteristics and changes and whatnot]].</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">You gain access to a pool of Mutation points to fuel various abilities over the course of the Awakening. The capacity of this pool is equal to your Monk level, and upon Awakening it contains points equal to half your Monk level + your Constitution modifier. As part of the action to Awaken the symbiote you can spend 3 Mutation Points to also activate the Rapid Reflexes mutation.</span></p><ul><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Gaining Points</strong> – Whenever you reduce a creature to 0 hitpoints with an unarmed attack you can absorb some of its essence to fuel your mutations. You add Mutation Points to your pool depending on the creature’s size:</span></p><ul><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">1 Point for a Tiny or Small creature</span></p></li><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">2 Points for a Medium creature</span></p></li><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">3 Points for a Large creature</span></p></li><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">4 Points for a Huge creature</span></p></li><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">5 Points for a Gargantuan or Larger creature.</span></p></li></ul></li><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Upkeep</strong> – Certain Mutation abilities require a continual upkeep of energy in addition to the up-front cost to trigger the effect. Upkeep is accomplished as a Free Action at the start of your turn. You can end a mutation at any time as a Free Action.</span></p></li></ul><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Variable Enhancement</strong> (2 Mutation Points, 1 point Upkeep) Pick one Simic Hybrid Animal Enhancement you do not already have. You have the benefits of that enhancement while this mutation is active.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Rapid Reflexes.</strong> (Bonus Action, 3 Mutation Points, 1 point Upkeep) You gain a +2 bonus to Armor Class and Advantage on Dexterity Saving Throws while this mutation is active.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Rapid Growth Barbs.</strong> (Free Action, 1 Mutation Point) You use Manifest Barbs once.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Heavy Barbs</strong> (Free Action, 1 Mutation Point, 1 point Upkeep) Your Barbs benefit from Hammerfists while this mutation is active.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Regeneration.</strong> (4 Mutation Points) As an Action, you regain 2d6 + Monk Level + Constitution Mod hitpoints.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Snap Out Of It.</strong> (2 Mutation Points) Once per turn as a Free Action you can gain Advantage on a Saving Throw to end an ongoing condition.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>I Can Take It.</strong> (2 Mutation Points) When you take damage, you can use your Reaction to reduce the damage by an amount equal to 1d6 + Monk Level + Constitution Mod</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">True Awakening</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">When you Truly Awaken the Symbiote, you fully relinquish control temporarily. [[TODO: List Physical Changes.]] You gain a Mutation Pool with a capacity of 2x your Monk level, but you must pay an upkeep of 1 Point at the start of each turn, even if you have no active mutations. If you have 0 points remaining in your pool after paying Upkeep at the start of your turn, True Awakening ends and you suffer the Toll.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Brutal Hammerfist.</strong> (Bonus Action, 3 Mutation Points, 2 point Upkeep, Mutually Exclusive with Vorpal Fists) Your speed is halved and attacks with your fists deal maximum damage while this mutation is active.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Vorpal Fists.</strong> (Bonus Action, Variable, Mutually Exclusive with Brutal Hammerfists) You hone your fists into extremely deadly weapons, causing effects based on the number of Mutation Points you spend according to the following chart (effects are cumulative, spending more points gets you that effect as well as every previous effect):</span></p><table class=\"MsoTableGrid\" border=\"1\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse;border:none;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-yfti-tbllook:1184;mso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><tbody><tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow:0;mso-yfti-firstrow:yes\"><td style=\"width:89.75pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">Initial Cost</span></p></td><td style=\"width:76.5pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-left:none;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">Upkeep</span></p></td><td style=\"width:301.25pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-left:none;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">Effect</span></p></td></tr><tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow:1\"><td style=\"width:89.75pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">3</span></p></td><td style=\"width:76.5pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">2</span></p></td><td style=\"width:301.25pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">Your Critical Hit Range is reduced by 2</span></p></td></tr><tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow:2\"><td style=\"width:89.75pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">4</span></p></td><td style=\"width:76.5pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">3</span></p></td><td style=\"width:301.25pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">You do an additional 2d10 damage on Critical Hits</span></p></td></tr><tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow:3\"><td style=\"width:89.75pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">5</span></p></td><td style=\"width:76.5pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">4</span></p></td><td style=\"width:301.25pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">Your Critical Hit Range is reduced by 4</span></p></td></tr><tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow:4;mso-yfti-lastrow:yes\"><td style=\"width:89.75pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">6</span></p></td><td style=\"width:76.5pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">5</span></p></td><td style=\"width:301.25pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\">You do an additional 4d10 damage on Critical Hits</span></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong> </strong></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Power Slam</strong>. (Action, 6 Mutation Points) Slam both fists in to the ground, causing a shockwave to radiate out. Each creature within 20 feet of you must make a Dexterity Saving Throw, suffering 8d10 Bludgeoning damage on a failed save, or half as much on a successful one. This damage can be modified by your Dragon Strike feature.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Fists of Fury.</strong> (Action, 6 Mutation Points) Move up to your speed, making as many attacks as possible while satisfying the following conditions: You must move at least 5 feet after making an attack, you must move in a direction that takes you further away from your starting position.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman',serif\"><strong>Barb Frenzy.</strong> (Action, 2 Mutation Points per creature targeted) You rapidly manifest and launch barbs at multiple creatures in range. Pick any number of creatures within 60 feet of you. For each creature, roll 1d4 and launch that many barb attacks at it. Once you use this ability, you can’t use it or Manifest Barbs again until the end of your Next Turn.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.dlRZPB0yfFmL3WbJ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_r3uvjq13w9"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675987936855,"modifiedTime":1677091157202,"lastModifiedBy":"gaqhLuQlqSyM3GkX"},"_id":"dlRZPB0yfFmL3WbJ","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Oz2iQtljCOeEAeBW":3}}
