{"name":"Indensian Warden's Staff","flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"type":"text"},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.itJSYwIXuCdef687"},"cf":{"id":"temp_77t4r2kc60q"}},"pages":[{"type":"text","name":"Indensian Warden's Staff","_id":"YPeZLBwNKuWwWl9F","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\">Initial Item</span></h2><h4><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\">Shillelagh-Infused Quarterstaff</span></h4><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Damage:</strong> 1d8 Bludgeoning</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\">Simple Weapon, One Handed, Magical, Use Wisdom for Attack/Damage</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\">Tier 1 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Aetheric Flow</strong> – This weapon can be used as a focus for casting spells.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Clawed Hand</strong> – Sharpened claws have been added to the grasping hand at the end of the staff. Melee attacks with the staff now deal an additional 1d4 slashing damage.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\">Tier 1 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Warden Spirit</strong> – The staff is imbued with a force of magic that functions as a Warden Spirit. You can call upon the spirit 4 times per day.</span></p><ul><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Empowering your Spirit</strong><br />Warden Spirits thrive on seeking out potential threats and ending them before they can become too great. At the DM’s discretion, ending a threat of sufficient significance can permanently empower the spirit, increasing the number of times you can call on it per day by 1. It may also be possible to undertake specific quests for the explicit purpose of strengthening your spirit.</span></p></li></ul><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Spirit of Retaliation</strong> – When a creature within 5 feet of you makes an attack against a target other than you, you can use your reaction to call upon the Warden Spirit to make an Opportunity Attack against the triggering creature.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Spirit of Potency</strong> – You gain a +1 Bonus to Weapon and Spell Attack and Damage rolls and the save DC of spells cast using the staff as a focus.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Spirit of Aggression</strong> – Once per turn when you hit a target with this staff you can use a free action to call upon your Warden Spirit to empower the strike. If you do, the attack deals an additional 2d6 force damage.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Spirit of Compassion</strong> – Any spell you cast that restores hitpoints heals for an additional 1d4.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\">Tier 2 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Sharpened Claws</strong> – The bonus slashing damage provided by Clawed Hand increases to 1d6.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\">Tier 2 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Strength of Spirit</strong> – You can call upon your Warden Spirit an additional 2 times per day.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Enhanced Potency</strong> – The bonus provided by your Spirit of Potency increases to +2.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Unchecked Aggression</strong> – The bonus damage dealt by your Spirit of Aggression increases to 3d6.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Welling Compassion</strong> – The bonus healing provided by your Spirit of Compassion increases to 1d6.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Advanced Retaliation</strong> – Your Spirit of Retaliation can now be used when you are hit with an attack by a creature within 5 feet of you.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\">Tier 3 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Razor Claws</strong> –The bonus slashing damage provided by Clawed Hand increases to 1d8.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\">Tier 3 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Strength of Spirit</strong> – You can call upon your Warden Spirit an additional 2 times per day.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Heightened Potency</strong> – The bonus provided by your Spirit of Potency increases to +3.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Unbridled Aggression</strong> – The bonus damage provided by your Spirit of Aggression increases to 4d6.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Boundless Compassion</strong> – The bonus healing provided by your Spirit of Compassion increases to 1d8.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Spirit of Tenacity</strong> – While wielding this staff you can take one additional reaction each round, provided you are able to take reactions.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Spirit of Overwhelming Force</strong> – When you take the attack action on your turn, prior to rolling the attack, you can use a free action to draw upon your Warden Spirit more fully than usual. By permanently reducing the maximum number of times you can call upon your Warden Spirit per day by 1 you can treat the number rolled on the die as a 20. Once you call upon the spirit in this way you can’t do so again until you finish a long rest.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false,"type":"text"}}}],"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671573681398,"modifiedTime":1677138049904,"lastModifiedBy":"8T9BvSXBp5qPtvBn"},"_id":"itJSYwIXuCdef687","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Oz2iQtljCOeEAeBW":3}}
{"name":"Bloodrot, Armor of the Damned","flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"pagetype":"text"},"scene-packer":{"hash":"041a28f527d4a9a326d918509ad1af9ace1ac322","sourceId":"JournalEntry.vFF8f78VJFuEWLO7","defaultPermission":2},"exportSource":{"world":"might-and-mercenaries","system":"dnd5e","coreVersion":"10.291","systemVersion":"2.1.4"},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.DnAk70y8axoRUN1T"},"cf":{"id":"temp_0t5s1gpbcib"}},"pages":[{"type":"text","name":"Bloodrot, Armor of the Damned","_id":"zgRR78FJkubC0kOW","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>Tier 1 Mundane</h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><strong>Bound in Chains</strong> – You gain a +1 bonus to Armor Class.</p><p><strong>Fluid Motion</strong> - You have advantage on dexterity saving throws.</p><h2>Tier 1 Magical</h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><strong>Bound Servant</strong> – You have learned to call upon the spirit of an imp that has been bound to the chain. As a one-hour ritual you may call the imp in to being as in the Find Familiar spell by taking 1d6 damage and using the resulting blood as the component for the ritual.</p><p><strong>Chained Protection</strong> - A small piece of chain hangs from your armor. When you or an ally within 5 feet of you is hit with a weapon attack, you can use your reaction to roll 1d4 and subtract the number rolled from the triggering attack roll.</p><h2>Tier 2 Mundane</h2><p><strong>Wrist Buckler</strong> - You are able to attach a standard shield to your forearm while keeping your hands free.</p><h2>Tier 2 Magical</h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><strong>Congealed Blood</strong> – You gain a +1 bonus to Armor Class and Saving Throws</p><p><strong>Bound Henchman</strong> – You can call upon your Infernal Conduit to tap in to the spirits bound within your armor. As an action you can spend 1 die from your Infernal Conduit pool to cast Summon Fey, Shadowspawn, or Undead at 4th level, using Charisma as your spellcasting stat. Roll the die and suffer that much Necrotic damage, using the resulting blood as the material component for the spell. You may empower this ability by using more dice from your Infernal Conduit pool. By spending 2 dice, you may cast the spell at 6th level.</p><h2>Tier 3 Mundane</h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><strong>Hardened Chains</strong> – You gain Resistance to non-magical Bludgeoning, Piercing, and Slashing damage.</p><h2>Tier 3 Magical</h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><strong>Coagulated Blood</strong> - The bonus from Congealed Blood increases to +2.</p><p><strong>Bound Soldier</strong> – You can call upon even greater spirits bound in the armor using your Infernal Conduit. As an action you can spend 2 dice from your Infernal Conduit pool to cast Summon Fiend at 6<sup>th</sup> level, using Charisma as your spellcasting stat. Roll the dice and suffer that much Necrotic damage, using the resulting blood as the material component for the spell. You may empower this ability by using more dice from your Infernal Conduit pool. By spending 3 dice, you may cast the spell at 8<sup>th</sup> level.</p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}}}],"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675302424472,"modifiedTime":1677091131912,"lastModifiedBy":"gaqhLuQlqSyM3GkX"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"eRgA1h4qRUhZdwPz":3},"_id":"jZjI1qUha3eTYWnt"}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_r3uvjq13w9","name":"Tuesday - Humanity's Pride","color":"#000000","fontColor":"#FFFFFF","icon":"","sorting":"m","contents":["AV2ZILYSO0uquOyp","FwAPT72AH6IFVTQ7","dlRZPB0yfFmL3WbJ"],"children":[]}},"pages":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"gaqhLuQlqSyM3GkX":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677091049417,"modifiedTime":1677091157202,"lastModifiedBy":"gaqhLuQlqSyM3GkX"},"_id":"lHTP4pwCkQoZrTf8"}
{"name":"Cillian's Prosthetic Arm","flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"pagetype":"text"},"scene-packer":{"hash":"0443d3870d38f3cfc669a5dabaefad6b81965c22","sourceId":"JournalEntry.KcY642CZ2JXctCw0","defaultPermission":2},"exportSource":{"world":"might-and-mercenaries","system":"dnd5e","coreVersion":"10.291","systemVersion":"2.1.4"},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.m3AkVec4t9fsONMn"},"cf":{"id":"temp_0o8y5afw0so"}},"pages":[{"type":"text","name":"Cillian's Prosthetic Arm","_id":"8AMLHF89MLtma867","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 1 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Rapid-Reaction Shield</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">—</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> When hit with an attack you can use your reaction to pop a shield our of the arm. You gain +2 AC against the triggering attack. As a Free Action you can also expend a Superiority Die. If you do, you gain a bonus equal to the roll of the Superiority Die +2 and the bonus lasts until the start of your next turn.</span></p><p>You can't use the Rapid-Reaction Shield while the Javelin launcher is deployed.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Javelin Launcher</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">—</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You can use a bonus action to deploy or retract the Javelin Launcher in your arm. You can launch a mini-javelin from the launcher in place of any attack you make. While the launcher is deployed, the Rapid-Reaction Shield can</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">’</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">t be used.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">Attack Bonus </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">—</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> 3 + Proficiency Bonus</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">Damage </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">—</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> 1d8 +3 Piercing</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">Range </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">—</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> 60/180</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">Ranged, Ammunition</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 1 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Technique Training</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">—</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You gain a +1 bonus to the DC of your Battle Master Maneuvers.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Lethality</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">—</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You gain a +1 bonus to Attack and Damage rolls with your Javelin Launcher.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 2 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Shield Bash:</strong> If your successfully block an attack with Rapid-Reaction Shield, you can spend a Superiority Die to try and interrupt the attacker. Make an attack against them, adding your Strength modifier, Proficiency Bonus, and the result of the Superiority Die to the attack roll. On a hit, you deal 1d6 + Strength bludgeoning damage and mildly concuss them, causing all of their spells to fail and attacks to miss until the end of their turn.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Enhanced Fletching</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">—</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You gain a +2 bonus to the base Attack and Damage rolls of your Javelin Launcher.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 2 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Improved Technique Training</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">—</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The bonus from Technique Training increases to +2.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Improved Lethality</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">—</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The bonus from Lethality increases to +2 and now applies to the attack you make with Shield Bash.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 3 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Greater Technique Training</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">—</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The bonus from Technique Training increases to +3.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Greater Lethality</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">—</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The bonus from Lethality increases to +3.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}}}],"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1673912863332,"modifiedTime":1677144226092,"lastModifiedBy":"8T9BvSXBp5qPtvBn"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"eRgA1h4qRUhZdwPz":3},"_id":"m9S2aKZ0Jjd1W9Qj"}
{"name":"Greataxe of Barbaric Fury","flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"pagetype":"text"},"scene-packer":{"hash":"f214ab0b83e609a75bfb9941a77d543028b8b03b","sourceId":"JournalEntry.LE28Rsqi1wesDosX","defaultPermission":2},"exportSource":{"world":"might-and-mercenaries","system":"dnd5e","coreVersion":"10.291","systemVersion":"2.1.4"},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.KabwAnmB8DXlvun4"},"cf":{"id":"temp_77t4r2kc60q"}},"pages":[{"type":"text","name":"Greataxe of Barbaric Fury","_id":"gVOQbRyuqoN9csdQ","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 1 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Reckless Rampage</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> When you Recklessly attack and hit with at least one attack, you may make an additional attack as a bonus action.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 1 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Lethality</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You gain a +1 bonus to Attack and Damage rolls.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 2 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Whirlwind Attack</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> As an action, make one weapon attack against each creature and object within 5 feet. If you reduce a creature to 0 hitpoints with this attack you may move towards another creature not yet targeted by this attack and repeat the attack, targeting each creature and object within 5 feet. This movement uses your standard movement for the turn and provokes opportunity attacks. You may repeat this pattern as long as you have remaining movement speed and a valid target to move to. You may not use Reckless Attack in conjunction with Whirlwind Attack.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 2 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Improved Lethality</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The bonus from Lethality increases to +2.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 3 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Rampaging Fury</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Reckless Rampage now allows you to make two attacks with your bonus action. Your Whirlwind Attack no longer needs to reduce a creature to 0 hitpoints for you to repeat the attack.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 3 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Greater Lethality</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The bonus from Lethality increases to +3. Your critical hit threshold is reduced by 1.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}}}],"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675455878609,"modifiedTime":1677136842406,"lastModifiedBy":"8T9BvSXBp5qPtvBn"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"eRgA1h4qRUhZdwPz":3},"_id":"ou1GfzbSKnE5uMAY"}
{"name":"Indensian Battle Plate of the Guardian","flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"type":"text"},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.pVX6WLkRn2iZ4TEv"},"cf":{"id":"temp_77t4r2kc60q"}},"pages":[{"type":"text","name":"Indensian Battle Plate of the Guardian","_id":"YPeZLBwNKuWwWl9F","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2><span style=\"font-family: 'Bookman Old Style',serif\">Initial Item</span></h2><h4><span style=\"font-family: 'Bookman Old Style',serif\">Indensian Battle Plate</span></h4><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Armor Class</strong> – 16 + Dexterity Bonus (Maximum 2)</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Bookman Old Style',serif\">Medium Armor, Disadvantage on Stealth</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family: 'Bookman Old Style',serif\">Tier 1 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Cleverly Designed Fittings</strong> – Particular care has been paid to ensuring this armor is as easy to put on as possible. You can don this armor unassisted in one minute. If you have the aid of two other capable creatures, the armor can be donned as an action.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Quick Release Buckles</strong> – When you want out of your armor, you usually want out sooner rather than later. These buckles make that possible, allowing you to doff it as an action.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family: 'Bookman Old Style',serif\">Tier 1 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Guardian Spirit</strong> – The armor is imbued with a force of magic that functions as a Guardian Spirit. You can call upon the spirit 4 times per day.</span></p><ul><li><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Empowering your Guardian Spirit</strong><br>Guardian Spirits are driven onwards by acts of heroism, bravery, and sacrifice in service to others. At the DM’s discretion, an act of sufficient significance can permanently empower the spirit, increasing the number of times you can call on it per day by 1. It may also be possible to undertake specific quests for the explicit purpose of strengthening your spirit.</span></p></li></ul><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Spirit of Resilience</strong> - When you suffer a critical hit, you can use your reaction to call upon your Guardian Spirit to bolster your defenses, granting you resistance to all damage from the triggering attack.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Spirit of Vigilance</strong> – While wearing this armor you can’t be surprised and enemies gain no benefit from being unseen when attacking you.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Spirit of Urgency</strong> – As a free action you can call upon your Guardian Spirit to assist you in putting on your armor, allowing you to don it as an action.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family: 'Bookman Old Style',serif\">Tier 2 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Strength of Spirit</strong> – You can call upon your Guardian Spirit an additional 2 times per day.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Spirit of Protection</strong> – You gain a +1 bonus to Armor Class and Saving Throws while wearing this armor.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Spirit of Stubbornness</strong> – While wearing this armor, you have advantage on death saving throws.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Spirit of Focus</strong> – When you cast a spell requiring concentration with a range of Self or that includes you as a target you can use a free action to call upon your Guardian Spirit for assistance. If you do, the spirit maintains concentration on the spell for the duration. You can have the spirit break concentration as a free action.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family: 'Bookman Old Style',serif\">Tier 3 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Strength of Spirit</strong> – You can call upon your Guardian Spirit an additional 2 times per day.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Unparalleled Protection</strong> – The bonus from your Spirit of Protection increases to +2.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Bookman Old Style',serif\"><strong>Spirit of Death’s Defiance</strong> – When you are reduced to 0 hitpoints but not killed outright, you can call upon your Guardian Spirit to try and save you. Roll a d20 and consult the following chart to see what happens. Prior to rolling, you can choose to draw upon the spirit more fully. By permanently reducing the maximum number of times you can call upon your Guardian Spirit per day by 1 you can treat the number rolled on the die as a 20. Once you call upon the spirit in this way you can’t do so again until you finish a long rest.</span></p><table class=\"MsoTableGrid\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse;border:none;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;\n mso-yfti-tbllook:1184;mso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><tbody><tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow:0;mso-yfti-firstrow:yes\"><td width=\"90\" valign=\"top\" style=\"width:67.25pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;\n  mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Bookman Old Style',serif\">1-4</span></p></td><td width=\"630\" valign=\"top\" style=\"width:472.25pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;\n  border-left:none;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:\n  solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Bookman Old Style',serif\">The spirit is unable to assist you.</span></p></td></tr><tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow:1\"><td width=\"90\" valign=\"top\" style=\"width:67.25pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;\n  border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;\n  padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Bookman Old Style',serif\">5-9</span></p></td><td width=\"630\" valign=\"top\" style=\"width:472.25pt;border-top:none;border-left:\n  none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;\n  mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;\n  mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Bookman Old Style',serif\">The spirit heals you for 2d8 + your Constitution modifier.</span></p></td></tr><tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow:2\"><td width=\"90\" valign=\"top\" style=\"width:67.25pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;\n  border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;\n  padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Bookman Old Style',serif\">10-14</span></p></td><td width=\"630\" valign=\"top\" style=\"width:472.25pt;border-top:none;border-left:\n  none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;\n  mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;\n  mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Bookman Old Style',serif\">The spirit heals you for 4d8 + Twice your Constitution modifier.</span></p></td></tr><tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow:3\"><td width=\"90\" valign=\"top\" style=\"width:67.25pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;\n  border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;\n  padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Bookman Old Style',serif\">15-19</span></p></td><td width=\"630\" valign=\"top\" style=\"width:472.25pt;border-top:none;border-left:\n  none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;\n  mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;\n  mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Bookman Old Style',serif\">The spirit heals you for half your total hitpoints and you gain resistance to all damage until the start of your next turn.</span></p></td></tr><tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow:4;mso-yfti-lastrow:yes\"><td width=\"90\" valign=\"top\" style=\"width:67.25pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;\n  border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;\n  padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Bookman Old Style',serif\">20</span></p></td><td width=\"630\" valign=\"top\" style=\"width:472.25pt;border-top:none;border-left:\n  none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;\n  mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;\n  mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Bookman Old Style',serif\">The spirit manifests in its full glory. You regain all your hitpoints, are cured of any negative conditions or ongoing effects, and can immediately take a full turn in combat. After this turn ends, initiative order resumes as normal.</span></p></td></tr></tbody></table>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false,"type":"text"}}}],"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671573681398,"modifiedTime":1677091154064,"lastModifiedBy":"gaqhLuQlqSyM3GkX"},"_id":"pVX6WLkRn2iZ4TEv","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Oz2iQtljCOeEAeBW":3}}
{"name":"Nightfall, Ferocity of the Moonwalker","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"Nightfall, Ferocity of the Moonwalker","type":"text","_id":"FSWmI40OZNTietvP","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Initial Item</span></h2><h4><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Great Club</span></h4><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Damage</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> 1d10 Bludgeoning</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">Two-Handed, Heavy, Martial Weapon, Primal Weapon</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\">Primal Weapon </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Attacks with a Primal Weapon can be made using Wisdom, rather than Strength or Dexterity.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 1 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Aetheric Flow</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> This weapon can be used as a focus for casting spells.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Warpriest Techniques</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You have a pool of technique points equal to your proficiency modifier + 2. You regain all spent points at the end of a short rest.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Deflective Technique</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Spend 1 Warpriest Technique point as an Action. You gain a +2 bonus to AC while wielding the club in both hands until you take a Short or Long Rest.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Hemorrhaging Technique</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Spend 1 Warpriest Technique point as an Action. Make a melee attack against a creature. On a hit, the creature takes 1d6 damage at the start of each of its turns for 3 rounds.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 1 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Puissance</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> You gain a +1 bonus to Attack rolls, Damage rolls, and the Save DC of spells made with the club.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Focused Mind Technique</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Spend 1 Warpriest Technique point as a Bonus Action. The next healing spell you cast on this turn also ends 1 Frightened or Charmed condition on the target.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 2 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Gnarled Branch </strong></span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The base damage of the club increases to 2d6.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Rapid Reflexes</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The bonus from your Deflective Technique increases to +3.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Reliable Hemorrhaging</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Your Hemorrhaging Technique is now Reliable. If you miss with the attack after using the technique, the technique point is refunded.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Concussive Technique</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Spend 1 Warpriest Technique point as a Free Action after hitting with a melee attack. The target of the attack must make a Constitution saving throw against your Spell DC. On a failure, the target is stunned until the start of your next turn. If the attack was a Critical Hit, the target automatically fails this save. Succeed or Fail, the target then becomes immune to this technique until the end of your next turn.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 2 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Improved Puissance</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The bonus from Puissance increases to +2.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Rapid Focus</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Your Focused Mind Technique is now a Free Action.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Path of Twilight Flames Technique</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Spend 1 Warpriest Technique point as an action. Cold flames spring up about your hooves for one minute. While these flames exist, your hooves deal an additional 1d8 radiant damage and whenever you move you can elect to leave behind a patch of radiant fire that persists until the flames around your hooves dissipate. When creatures of your choice enter the fire for the first time on a turn or start their turn there, they take 1d8 radiant damage.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 3 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Petrified Branch</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The base damage of the club increases to 3d6.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Deep Hemorrhaging</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The damage from your Hemorrhaging Technique increases to 2d6.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Vigilant Technique</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Spend 1 Warpriest Technique point as a free action when you use Vigilant Blessing, causing it to apply to a number of creatures equal to your proficiency bonus.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 3 Magical Enhancements</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Greater Puissance</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The bonus from Puissance increases to +3.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Twilight Inferno</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The damage dealt by your Path of Twilight Flames increases to 2d8.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Wings of Twilight Technique</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Spend 1 Warpriest Technique point as a free action when you use Steps of Night, causing it to target a number of creatures equal to your Proficiency Bonus.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.s4xyrfTblr0QvFpO"},"cf":{"id":"temp_0t5s1gpbcib"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1673412750379,"modifiedTime":1677091124629,"lastModifiedBy":"gaqhLuQlqSyM3GkX"},"_id":"s4xyrfTblr0QvFpO","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Oz2iQtljCOeEAeBW":3}}
{"name":"Sapphie's Battle Dress","flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"pagetype":"text"},"scene-packer":{"hash":"b875fdd237f8ce9c42dd341b02512710ebaaa003","sourceId":"JournalEntry.egbcUXSdnnt8VRuG"},"exportSource":{"world":"might-and-mercenaries","system":"dnd5e","coreVersion":"10.291","systemVersion":"2.1.4"},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.9dTf4ybdQPFB2O9Z"},"cf":{"id":"temp_77t4r2kc60q"}},"pages":[{"type":"text","name":"Sapphie's Battle Dress","_id":"uLJ6vt7aekSQP8jt","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 1 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Mithril Weave</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Mithril filaments have been woven through the regular fibers of the dress, providing an Armor Class of 13 + Dexterity modifier.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 1 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Essence Weaving</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> Essence infused threads have been woven throughout the dress. You gain a magical +1 bonus to Armor Class and Saving Throws.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Focused Mind</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> When you need to make a Constitution Saving Throw to maintain Concentration on a spell, you can choose to automatically succeed instead. You can do this a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus and regain all uses at the end of a long rest.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Pocket of Plenty</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">– Whenever you reach in to this pocket you find food, even if you don't remember putting it there.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 2 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Glamerweave</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The regular fibers of the dress have been replaced with Common Glamerweave, allowing for basic illusory patterns to be manifested within or rising from the cloth. When you make a Charisma Ability Check, you can roll 1d4 and add it to the result. You may do this a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus, and you regain all uses at the end of a long rest.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 2 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Essence Infusion</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The magical bonus from Essence Weaving increases to +2.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 3 Mundane</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Uncommon Glamerweave</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The Glamerweave within the dress has been further enhanced. You now add 1d6 to every Charisma Ability Check you make while wearing the dress.</span></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:EBGaramond-Regular\">Tier 3 Magical</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\"><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"><strong>Essence Infusion</strong> </span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Bold\">–</span><span style=\"font-family:CrimsonText-Regular\"> The magical bonus from Essence Weaving increases to +3.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}}}],"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1676062939574,"modifiedTime":1677091159550,"lastModifiedBy":"gaqhLuQlqSyM3GkX"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"eRgA1h4qRUhZdwPz":3},"_id":"w0WY6Agn9Lmy4tSF"}
